<h1>CodeInterviewPro - Technical Project Documentation</h1>

<div class="highlight">
  <p><strong>CodeInterviewPro</strong> is a cutting-edge, AI-driven technical interview platform designed to facilitate seamless, real-time coding assessments. It empowers interviewers and candidates to collaborate in real-time with live code synchronization, integrated video/audio communication, and an advanced, secure multi-language code execution engine.</p>
  <p>To ensure the highest quality of evaluation, CodeInterviewPro employs a <strong>Dual-AI Evaluation System</strong> utilizing Google Gemini and CodeBert to provide instant, human-like feedback, complexity scoring, and plagiarism detection.</p>
</div>

<h2>1. Key Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Real-Time Code Collaboration:</strong> Built with WebSockets (SignalR) to instantly sync code editor typing between the candidate and the interviewer.</li>
    <li><strong>Integrated Video &amp; Audio:</strong> Peer-to-peer WebRTC integration enables live face-to-face communication without requiring third-party tools.</li>
    <li><strong>Secure Code Execution Pipeline:</strong> Safely compiles and executes user-submitted code in multiple languages (C#, Python, Java, Go, JS) using sandboxed, ephemeral Docker containers.</li>
    <li><strong>Dual-AI Evaluation:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>CodeBert:</strong> Performs deep AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) analysis, calculates cyclomatic complexity, and checks code similarity (plagiarism detection).</li>
            <li><strong>Google Gemini:</strong> Acts as a virtual senior interviewer, taking the code, CodeBert's metrics, and test case results to generate a human-readable performance report and hiring recommendation.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Asynchronous AI Processing:</strong> Uses an in-memory Background Task Queue to process heavy AI requests without blocking the user interface, resulting in a smooth user experience.</li>
    <li><strong>High Performance &amp; Rate Limiting:</strong> Utilizes Redis for caching code execution results and API rate limiting to ensure optimal performance under heavy load.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Technology Stack</h2>
<h3>Backend</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> .NET 8 (C#) adhering to Clean Architecture principles</li>
    <li><strong>Database:</strong> Microsoft SQL Server with Entity Framework Core</li>
    <li><strong>Caching &amp; Rate Limiting:</strong> Redis</li>
    <li><strong>Real-time Comms:</strong> SignalR (WebSockets)</li>
    <li><strong>Code Execution:</strong> Docker Engine Integration via <code>/var/run/docker.sock</code></li>
</ul>

<h3>Frontend</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Angular (Standalone Components architecture)</li>
    <li><strong>Styling:</strong> Tailwind CSS &amp; Custom CSS</li>
    <li><strong>Code Editor:</strong> Monaco Editor</li>
    <li><strong>Video/Audio:</strong> WebRTC browser APIs</li>
</ul>

<h3>AI &amp; Machine Learning</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Generative AI:</strong> Google Gemini API (<code>gemini-3-flash-preview</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Code Analysis Model:</strong> CodeBert (Hosted locally via a Python microservice)</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Architecture Overview</h2>
<p>The system is designed with <strong>Clean Architecture</strong> for maximum separation of concerns:</p>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Domain Layer:</strong> Contains core entities (User, InterviewSession, ExecutionResult) and enums. This is the heart of the business logic.</li>
    <li><strong>Application Layer:</strong> Contains DTOs, interfaces, and core business rules. It has no dependencies on external frameworks.</li>
    <li><strong>Infrastructure Layer:</strong> Handles all external concerns: Entity Framework DbContext, Redis caching, Docker code execution integration, and external AI service clients.</li>
    <li><strong>API Layer:</strong> ASP.NET Core REST API exposing secure, JWT-authenticated endpoints.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Code Execution Security</h3>
<p>Executing untrusted code is inherently risky. CodeInterviewPro handles this by:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Receiving code at the API level.</li>
    <li>Communicating directly with the host's Docker daemon.</li>
    <li>Spinning up a temporary <code>code-runner</code> container with complete network isolation.</li>
    <li>Enforcing strict limits on memory (e.g., 256MB) and execution time (e.g., 30 seconds) using cancellation tokens.</li>
    <li>Destroying the container immediately after execution to prevent accumulation of stale data.</li>
</ol>

<h2>4. Testing &amp; DevOps</h2>
<p>The platform is containerized using Docker and Docker Compose, making deployment and orchestration highly scalable. Additionally, the execution engine's performance is verified using a comprehensive <strong>k6</strong> stress-testing suite to ensure the system can handle concurrent interview sessions without latency spikes.</p>

